  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Current role implementations do not forbid renouncing of own role in case there are no more addresses with the same role. Considering the `onlyRole` modifier in the `addRole(address account)`  functions, there is a possibility to stuck in a situation when there are no more roles left. I'd propose to add an additional check to the `remove()` function of the [Roles](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/blob/master/contracts/access/Roles.sol) library ensuring that there is at least one address with an assigned role left.\r\n",
